    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of the Navy (
                        Sullivan
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d848</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">848</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-12-09T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="848" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d848">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/12–948</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sullivan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-09">9 December
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Referring to my letter of 2
                    December requesting State Department’s comments on certain questions with
                    relation to China, it is requested that your answer cover the matters raised in
                    Vice Admiral Badger’s despatch No. 080145Z, copy of which has been furnished you
                        previously.<note n="3" xml:id="d848fn3">Not found in Department
                        files.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Particular attention is invited to Admiral Badger’s assumption that his objective
                    in providing protection to United States Nationals is “to safeguard U. S.
                    Nationals and their properties in China to the limit of feasibility during any
                    temporary loss of government control and police protection.”</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John</hi> L. <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
